# ratatui-image Widget APIs

Based on the source code, here's how to use the `Image` and `StatefulImage` widgets:

## Image Widget (Stateless)

The `Image` widget is immutable and doesn't adapt to area changes:

```rust
pub struct Image<'a> {
    image: &'a Protocol,
}

impl<'a> Image<'a> {
    pub fn new(image: &'a Protocol) -> Image<'a> {
        Image { image }
    }
}
```

**Usage example:**
```rust
struct App {
    image_static: Protocol,
}

fn ui(f: &mut Frame<'_>, app: &mut App) {
    let image = Image::new(&app.image_static);
    f.render_widget(image, f.size());
}
```

## StatefulImage Widget (Stateful)

The `StatefulImage` widget adapts to rendering area changes and supports resizing:

```rust
pub struct StatefulImage {
    resize: Resize,
    background_color: Option<Rgb<u8>>,
}

impl StatefulImage {
    pub fn new(background_color: Option<Rgb<u8>>) -> StatefulImage
    pub fn resize(mut self, resize: Resize) -> StatefulImage
}
```

**Usage example:**
```rust
struct App {
    image_state: StatefulProtocol,
}

fn ui(f: &mut Frame<'_>, app: &mut App) {
    let image = StatefulImage::new(None).resize(Resize::Crop(None));
    f.render_stateful_widget(image, f.size(), &mut app.image_state);
}
```

## Resize Strategies

Two modes are available: `Fit` (maintains aspect ratio) and `Crop` (clips edges with customizable sides).

